      "module_path": "dry_check::approval_interactor",
      "docs": "Implements `DryCheckApprovalService`. Updated for D5: now reads DryCheckCoverageRecord via DryCheckCoveragePort for staleness checking instead of performing embedding/similarity-search. Staleness check includes four conditions: (1) all current FragmentRefs must be present in the stored coverage, (2) the stored config_fingerprint must match the current_config_fingerprint injected at construction (config change → Blocked), (3) the stored corpus_fingerprint must match the current_corpus_fingerprint injected at construction (corpus change → Blocked), and (4) either stored coverage fingerprint being the fail-closed sentinel (all-zero) blocks. For all-resolved checking it reads DryCheckReader history, derives the same latest-per-pair last-write-wins view as DryCheckResultsInteractor, and evaluates only latest records whose pair_key is present in coverage.processed_pair_keys and that touch current FragmentRef values. Holds DryCheckReader + DryCheckCoveragePort + current_config_fingerprint + current_corpus_fingerprint as private fields.",
      "spec_refs": [
        {
