      "module_path": "dry_check::services",
      "docs": "Application service for the cheap dry gate approval check after D5. The caller supplies the active track_id and current diff FragmentRef set. Decides Approved/Blocked using DryCheckCoveragePort (staleness check: (1) are all current FragmentRefs present in coverage, (2) does the stored config_fingerprint match the current config fingerprint — a mismatch means the config changed and coverage is stale, (3) does the stored corpus_fingerprint match the current corpus fingerprint — a mismatch means the corpus changed (file added/removed/modified) and coverage is stale, and (4) either stored coverage fingerprint being the fail-closed sentinel blocks) + DryCheckReader (all-resolved check scoped to latest records whose pair_key is in coverage.processed_pair_keys and that touch the current diff), with no embedding or semantic-index lookup. DryCheckReader history is interpreted as latest-per-pair with last-write-wins, so a later Accepted/NotAViolation can resolve an older Violation for the same pair.",
      "spec_refs": [
        {
